Setup and Installation
1. Install Dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt
This will install all the required packages listed in your requirements.txt file (fastapi, uvicorn, scikit-learn, pandas, numpy, joblib, streamlit, pydantic, seaborn, matplotlib, plotly, requests, pytest).
Running the Project
2. Train the Model (if needed):
python src/train_model.py
This will train your fraud detection model using the creditcard.csv dataset.
3. Start the FastAPI Backend:
hpython src/main.py
Or alternatively:
uvicorn src.main:app --reload
This starts the API server (usually on http://localhost:8000).
4. Run the Streamlit Frontend:
streamlit run src/streamlit_app.py
This opens the web interface (usually on http://localhost:8501).
Testing
5. Run Tests:
python test_api.py
Or if using pytest:
pytest